      "side": 1,
      "message": "I first figured I\u0027d just allow prevColor \u003d GrColor4f::kIllegalConstructor in the .fp file. That\u0027s ugly, though, because sksl has to understand at least enough C++ syntax and tokens to handle that, and inevitably I\u0027ll have to extend it for every such value we end up needing.\n\nMy next attempt was to use @initializers { prevColor(GrColor4f::kIllegalConstructor) }, but the problem is that prevColor isn\u0027t defined in the class because it\u0027s a private variable, so that doesn\u0027t actually work. I spent a few hours trying to move private variables into the class before deciding it was more trouble than it was worth, and ultimately settled on this as a quick inoffensive hack to at least get it working for now.\n\nI am not proud of this and completely agree we\u0027re going to need a better solution, but I wanted to let it simmer for a while.",
